    <h1>Privacy Policy for Tiny PDF Shrinker</h1>
    <p><strong>Last Updated: March 19, 2025</strong></p>
    
    <div class="highlight">
        <p>At Tiny PDF Shrinker, we take your privacy seriously. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and handle your information when you use our mobile application.</p>
    </div>
    
    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    
    <h3>1.1 Information You Provide</h3>
    <p>When you use Tiny PDF Shrinker, we may collect the following types of information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>PDF files and images that you choose to process through our application</li>
        <li>User-generated content within the application, such as saved documents</li>
        <li>App preferences and settings you configure</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>1.2 Information Collected Automatically</h3>
    <p>We may automatically collect certain information when you use our app:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>App usage statistics and interaction data</li>
        <li>Device information (such as device model, operating system version)</li>
        <li>Performance data and error logs</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>To provide and maintain our services</li>
        <li>To process your PDF files and images as requested</li>
        <li>To improve and optimize our application</li>
        <li>To personalize your experience</li>
        <li>To identify and fix bugs or issues</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>3. Storage and Processing of Files</h2>
    <p>Tiny PDF Shrinker processes PDF files and images directly on your device. We do not upload or store your documents on our servers. All processing (including PDF compression, merging, splitting, OCR, and document scanning) occurs locally on your device.</p>
    
    <p>When you use features that require access to your device's storage or camera:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Files are accessed only with your explicit permission</li>
        <li>Processed files are saved to locations you specify</li>
        <li>We do not retain copies of your files beyond what's necessary for the app's functionality</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>4. Permissions We Request</h2>
    <p>Tiny PDF Shrinker requires certain permissions to function properly:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Storage access</strong>: To read and write PDF files to your device storage</li>
        <li><strong>Camera</strong>: For document scanning features</li>
        <li><strong>Internet</strong>: For in-app review functionality and error reporting</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You can revoke these permissions at any time through your device settings, though this may limit app functionality.</p>
    
    <h2>5. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties, except in the following limited circumstances:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Service Providers</strong>: We may share information with third-party vendors who help us provide the service (such as analytics providers).</li>
        <li><strong>Compliance with Laws</strong>: We may disclose information when required by applicable law, regulation, or legal process.</li>
        <li><strong>Business Transfers</strong>: In the event of a merger, acquisition, or asset sale, user information may be transferred as a business asset.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>6. Google Play Services</h2>
    <p>Our app uses Google Play Services, including Google Play Core libraries for in-app reviews. Google's privacy practices are governed by their own privacy policy, which you can view at <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>.</p>
    
    <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>Tiny PDF Shrinker is not directed to children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe we have collected information from your child, please contact us so we can promptly remove the information.</p>
    
    <h2>8. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
    <p>Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Access, correct, or delete your personal information</li>
        <li>Object to or restrict certain processing of your data</li>
        <li>Data portability</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise these rights, please contact us using the information provided below.</p>
    
    <h2>9. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, including to satisfy legal requirements or reporting obligations.</p>
    
    <h2>10. Security</h2>
    <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect the information we collect and maintain. However, no security system is impenetrable, and we cannot guarantee the security of our systems 100%.</p>
    
    <h2>11. International Data Transfers</h2>
    <p>Your information may be transferred to, and maintained on, computers located outside of your state, province, country, or other governmental jurisdiction where the data protection laws may differ from those of your jurisdiction.</p>
    
    <h2>12. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.</p>
    
    <h2>13. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions or suggestions about our Privacy Policy or practices, please contact us at:</p>
    <p>[Your Contact Information]</p>
    
